06/05/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- NATO's Euro-Atlantic Disaster Response Co-ordination Centre and the Croatian government will organise a civilian drill in Zadar from May 19th-24th, with the goal of co-ordinating disaster relief efforts.
Around 1,000 representatives from 35 partner states will participate.
The UN Office for the Co-ordination of Humanitarian Affairs is also contributing to the preparation of the event.
(Poslovni dnevnik, NATO website - 06/05/07)
